Considerations for licensors: Our public licenses are intended for use by
those authorized to give the public permission to use material in ways
otherwise restricted by copyright and certain other rights. Our licenses
are irrevocable. Licensors should read and understand the terms and
conditions before applying one of our licenses.

Considerations for the public: By using one of our public licenses, a
licensor grants the public permission to use the licensed material under
specified terms and conditions. If the licensor's permission is not
necessary for any reason (for example, because of any applicable
exception or limitation to copyright), then that use is not regulated by
the license. The license grants only permissions under copyright and
certain other rights that a licensor has authority to grant.

